						<summary>

						<p>On the south wall, central shrine, Umāmahēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Year: lost.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription is a label explaining an image. It states that it is that of Śāttaṉ Guṇabhattaṉ <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Haracharaṇa-śēkharaṉ of Ālattūr, who had also been honoured with the title, <hi rend="italic">Rājakēsari-mūvēndavēḷār</hi> who built the temple in stone, possibly under the direction of Uḍaiya-pirāṭṭiyār, mother of Madhurāntakadēva <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Uttamachōḷa.</p>						

						<p>Published in <hi rend="italic">S.I.I.,</hi> Vol. III No. 147.</p>						

						</summary>
